.TH ReleaseMB 3X
.SH NAME
\*LReleaseMB \*O\(em Command to release any mouse button.
.SH SYNOPSIS
\*LReleaseMB\*O
\*V[ModifierList]* Button\*O
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
\*LReleaseMB\*O
command will simulate the releasing of a button on the standard mouse.
This release maybe modified by any of the standard X modifiers (any
combination). This function is usually accompanied by doing a
\*LLocatePointer\*O first to a region which accepts mouse input and performing
a \*LPressMB\*O.
.IP "\*V[ModifierList]*\*O" 14n
List of modifiers to modify the mouse button release. For a full list
of available Modifiers see \*LModifierList(3X)\*O. The default is no modifiers.
.IP "\*VButton\*O"
Button to be pressed. For a full list of available Buttons
see \*LButtonList(3X)\*O.
.PP
For more information about \*LReleaseMB\*O, see
the \*EOSF/Motif Quality Assurance Test Suite User's Guide\*O
.SH EXAMPLE
\*LReleaseMB <Shift> <Ctrl> Btn1\*O
.PP
This will release mouse Button1 with Control and Shift modifiers.
.SH "RELATED INFORMATION"
.na
\*LLocatePointer(3X)\*O, \*LPressMB(3X)\*O, \*LClickMB(3X)\*O,
\*LButtonList(3X)\*O, \*LModifierList(3X)\*O
.ad
